    "created_at": "2014-07-29T21:29:32Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-07-29T21:29:32Z",
    "body": "> &'static str is also a &'a str for any 'a\n\nI see, `&'static str` can be \"re-borrowed\" as `&'a str` for any `a` because `&'static str` is always available (or in other words `a` is always \"shorter\" than or equal to `static`). For some reason, I always forget that the compiler can do that.\n\nI was analyzing the issue from the other way: that `&'a str` would have to be \"upgraded\" to `&'static str`, which is not possible.\n\nThanks for the explanation @huonw! My misunderstanding, closing.\n",
